---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'Why not just use Goodreads?',
    a: 'Goodreads conflates shelves with reading state and user lists. When you own 500 books across overlapping shelves, you can\'t cleanly answer "what do I own?" Casebound treats your library as a canonical catalog and lists as tags layered on top. They\'re separate things, and they look that way.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is my reading data private by default?',
    a: 'Yes. Per-book privacy toggle, no public profile by default, no social feed. You decide what \u2014 if anything \u2014 is visible.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Will there be social features?',
    a: 'Possibly. Light friend-library viewing and shared lists are on the roadmap for a later version. Casebound will never be primarily a social product.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Will there be a web app?',
    a: 'Mobile first. Web comes later if it\u2019s clearly needed.',
  },
];
---

<section class="bg-casebound-wallpaper px-6 py-16 sm:py-24">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="font-serif font-medium text-2xl sm:text-[32px] mb-10 leading-snug">
      Frequently asked questions
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-4">
      {faqs.map((faq) => (
        <details class="group border border-casebound-border rounded-lg bg-casebound-paper">
          <summary class="cursor-pointer px-6 py-4 font-medium text-base sm:text-[17px] flex items-center justify-between gap-4 list-none [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
            <span>{faq.q}</span>
            <span class="shrink-0 text-casebound-muted transition-transform group-open:rotate-45 text-xl leading-none" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-[15px] sm:text-base leading-relaxed text-casebound-muted">
            {faq.a}
          </div>
        </details>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
